<summary>
## Summary: Bug: archive-on-completion stub missing status:"done" and title

### Changes Implemented
1. **`archival-service.ts`**: Changed the archival cycle from calling `featureLoader.delete()` (which deleted the entire feature directory, leaving nothing) to calling `featureLoader.archiveFeature()` (which moves data to `.automaker/archive/` and writes a proper stub). Also updated the `feature:archived` event emission to include `archivePath`, and updated log/comment text.

2. **`feature-loader.ts`**: Already had two fixes in place in this worktree:
   - **`archiveFeature()` method** (lines 756–870): Copies `feature.json`, `agent-output.md`, and `handoff-*.json` to the archive directory, deletes the original directory, then writes a stub `{ id, archived: true, archivedAt, archivePath, status: "done", title }` — ensuring the stub always includes `status` and `title`.
   - **`normalizeFeature()` guard** (lines 66–71): If `archived === true`, always forces `status: 'done'` regardless of what the stub file contains. This prevents LE state machine from treating archived stubs as active work items.

3. **`archival-service.test.ts`**: Updated all test assertions from `featureLoader.delete` → `featureLoader.archiveFeature`, updated the `feature:archived` event expectation to include `archivePath`, added a new test verifying `delete` is NOT called (features are archived, not removed), and updated test descriptions/comments to reflect the new behavior.

### Files Modified
- `apps/server/src/services/archival-service.ts`
- `apps/server/tests/unit/services/archival-service.test.ts`
- *(feature-loader.ts was already correct — no changes needed)*

### Risks/Blockers Encountered
- **Pre-existing build errors**: `src/lib/otel.ts` (OTLPTraceExporter type mismatch) and `src/services/ledger-service.ts` (`entryType` property on `MetricsLedgerRecord`) fail TypeScript compilation. Neither file is in scope for this feature and neither appears in `git status`. These are pre-existing and not introduced by this work.

### Learnings
- The worktree already had `archiveFeature()` implemented in `feature-loader.ts` along with the `archived` guard in `normalizeFeature()`. The missing piece was the `archival-service.ts` still calling `delete` instead of `archiveFeature`.
- Always read files from the correct worktree path — the main repo at `/Users/kj/dev/automaker/` had a different (more advanced) version of the files than the feature worktree.

### Notes for Developer
- The `otel.ts` and `ledger-service.ts` build errors are pre-existing and block `npm run build:server`. These are unrelated to this feature and should be fixed separately.
- Fix 3 from the feature description ("In the LE state machine intake, skip features with `archived: true`") is documented in the feature spec but not listed in "Files to Modify" — it may already be handled by the `normalizeFeature` guard or may be addressed in a separate feature.

### Verification Status
- **61/61 tests pass** for `archival-service.test.ts` (12 tests) and `feature-loader.test.ts` (49 tests).
- Playwright verification not applicable: this is a background server service with no UI surface.
- Build fails on 2 pre-existing TypeScript errors in unrelated files (`otel.ts`, `ledger-service.ts`). Our modified files (`archival-service.ts`, `feature-loader.ts`) have no TypeScript errors.
</summary>